        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1945-08-14T14:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1945-08-14T14:00:00-05:00" n="451" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d451">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">103.9151: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Ambassador in Bolivia</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Thurston</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1945-08-14T15:00:00-04:00">August 14, 1945—3 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>541. Munro RDC [from] Utz.<note n="66" xml:id="d451fn66">F. W. Utz, Vice
                        President, Rubber Development Corporation.</note> Reourtel 265 April 19,
                    1945. For obvious reasons, you are hereby instructed to inform appropriate
                    Bolivian governmental authorities, through the Embassy, that the offer
                    heretofore made on behalf of Rubber Development Corporation to extend rubber
                    agreement, price premium, and other collateral agreements to June 30, 1947, is
                    withdrawn, effective immediately. [Utz.]</p>
                <p>For Emb from Dept. Dept concurs in foregoing. Emb is requested to assist RDC in
                    withdrawing offer to extend rubber agreements.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Byrnes</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
